WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:26.776 --> 00:00:28.403 position:50% align:center
[G-BOYS, RED ANGELS grunting]

00:00:28.486 --> 00:00:29.612 position:50% align:center
Die!

00:00:29.696 --> 00:00:34.701 position:50% align:center
[grunting continues]

00:00:37.120 --> 00:00:38.455 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE INTERVIEWER A]
Ikebukuro's Civil War

00:00:38.538 --> 00:00:40.457 position:50% align:center
has already claimed one life.

00:00:40.540 --> 00:00:42.917 position:50% align:center
Many more have been
injured or arrested.

00:00:43.001 --> 00:00:44.627 position:50% align:center
Not to mention
ordinary civilians

00:00:44.711 --> 00:00:46.713 position:50% align:center
have also gotten caught
up in the crossfire.

00:00:46.796 --> 00:00:49.299 position:50% align:center
They've been attacked simply
for wearing red or blue.

00:00:49.382 --> 00:00:50.300 position:50% align:center
Why go so far?

00:00:50.383 --> 00:00:52.135 position:50% align:center
Jeez, ain't it obvious, lady?

00:00:52.218 --> 00:00:55.013 position:50% align:center
It's because you don't take any
chances with a rotten G-Boy!

00:00:55.096 --> 00:00:57.766 position:50% align:center
[RED ANGELS cheer]

00:00:57.849 --> 00:00:59.267 position:50% align:center
The mob we're up
against are the ones

00:00:59.351 --> 00:01:01.269 position:50% align:center
who crossed the line first.

00:01:01.353 --> 00:01:03.313 position:50% align:center
If we don't fight back,
we're as good as dead.

00:01:03.396 --> 00:01:07.525 position:50% align:center
[G-BOYS yell]

00:01:07.609 --> 00:01:10.236 position:50% align:center
[KYOUICHI] These streets are
no stranger to violence.

00:01:10.320 --> 00:01:14.657 position:50% align:center
It's business as usual,
except now it has a name.

00:01:14.741 --> 00:01:18.536 position:50% align:center
As long as the law says you're
allowed to defend yourself,

00:01:18.620 --> 00:01:20.121 position:50% align:center
that's what you do.

00:01:20.205 --> 00:01:23.083 position:50% align:center
There's no room for
pacifism in this town.

00:01:23.166 --> 00:01:24.876 position:50% align:center
The only way we're gonna
settle this cleanly

00:01:24.959 --> 00:01:27.587 position:50% align:center
would be if we could get
our hands on some guns,

00:01:27.671 --> 00:01:30.298 position:50% align:center
and light it up like the
kids in America do.

00:01:30.382 --> 00:01:32.050 position:50% align:center
[RED ANGELS yell]

00:01:32.133 --> 00:01:33.426 position:50% align:center
If the King wasn't laid-out,

00:01:33.510 --> 00:01:35.637 position:50% align:center
then we could've
talked it over with him.

00:01:35.720 --> 00:01:39.057 position:50% align:center
But the G-Boys don't have
a leader to rein 'em in now,

00:01:39.140 --> 00:01:40.642 position:50% align:center
so we'll have to
put 'em in their place

00:01:40.725 --> 00:01:42.185 position:50% align:center
until they calm down.

00:01:42.268 --> 00:01:44.229 position:50% align:center
What about the photo people
are sharing online

00:01:44.312 --> 00:01:47.273 position:50% align:center
of the alleged moment
he was shot?

00:01:47.357 --> 00:01:49.984 position:50% align:center
Apparently, there's a rumor
that your band of followers

00:01:50.068 --> 00:01:50.985 position:50% align:center
were behind the hit.

00:01:51.069 --> 00:01:52.737 position:50% align:center
It's not true.

00:01:52.821 --> 00:01:56.449 position:50% align:center
And personally, I'd like to
know what really happened.

00:01:56.533 --> 00:01:59.035 position:50% align:center
[KAORU sobs]

00:01:59.119 --> 00:02:02.247 position:50% align:center
Be careful.
That's my big brother.

00:02:02.330 --> 00:02:04.457 position:50% align:center
Please be okay!

00:02:04.541 --> 00:02:07.252 position:50% align:center
You hear that, world!
Ikebukuro is ours!

00:02:07.335 --> 00:02:12.340 position:50% align:center
[RED ANGELS cheer]

00:02:40.243 --> 00:02:43.538 position:50% align:center
Makoto... Where are you?

00:02:48.918 --> 00:02:51.171 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
Saru, it's me.

00:02:51.254 --> 00:02:53.882 position:50% align:center
[SARU] Did you really call
me from a payphone?

00:02:53.965 --> 00:02:55.717 position:50% align:center
What happened to your cell?

00:02:55.800 --> 00:02:58.094 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO] If I use it,
they'll know where I am.

00:02:58.178 --> 00:03:00.597 position:50% align:center
Can you please just fill me in?

00:03:00.680 --> 00:03:02.515 position:50% align:center
It's starting to get worse.

00:03:02.599 --> 00:03:05.060 position:50% align:center
It's the Kyougokukai of Kansai.

00:03:05.143 --> 00:03:07.854 position:50% align:center
They're offering to supply
firearms to the Red Angels.

00:03:07.937 --> 00:03:08.938 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO gasps]

00:03:09.022 --> 00:03:11.566 position:50% align:center
[SARU]
The yakuza suggested it first,

00:03:11.649 --> 00:03:15.570 position:50% align:center
and their new clients
gladly accepted.

00:03:15.653 --> 00:03:18.948 position:50% align:center
So, as a countermeasure,
the newly orphaned G-Boys

00:03:19.032 --> 00:03:21.951 position:50% align:center
are supposedly going to partner
up with the Hidaka Group.

00:03:22.035 --> 00:03:23.828 position:50% align:center
Wait, is that
actually happening?

00:03:23.912 --> 00:03:25.455 position:50% align:center
[SARU]
Get real!

00:03:25.538 --> 00:03:27.999 position:50% align:center
Still though. If you're
looking for a perfect pitch

00:03:28.083 --> 00:03:29.959 position:50% align:center
to push your gun sales with,

00:03:30.043 --> 00:03:31.753 position:50% align:center
there's nothing
better than a rumor.

00:03:31.836 --> 00:03:33.213 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO grunts]

00:03:33.296 --> 00:03:34.422 position:50% align:center
What's next?

00:03:34.506 --> 00:03:36.758 position:50% align:center
If you're gonna make
a move, I'll help you.

00:03:36.841 --> 00:03:38.218 position:50% align:center
No thanks.

00:03:38.301 --> 00:03:41.054 position:50% align:center
I have to lie low 'til I can
suss out the big picture.

00:03:41.137 --> 00:03:43.515 position:50% align:center
One wrong move, and I
could step into a trap.

00:03:46.226 --> 00:03:48.603 position:50% align:center
[LIN] Your mother's
regained consciousness.

00:03:48.687 --> 00:03:50.897 position:50% align:center
Guo's been looking after her.

00:03:50.980 --> 00:03:52.482 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
Good.

00:03:52.565 --> 00:03:55.318 position:50% align:center
They're both safe at the moment,
but rightly worried about you.

00:03:55.402 --> 00:03:57.737 position:50% align:center
Would you like me to deliver
a message to them?

00:03:57.821 --> 00:03:59.656 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO] Nah. If you can
keep an eye on them

00:03:59.739 --> 00:04:01.658 position:50% align:center
for me though,
I'd appreciate it.

00:04:01.741 --> 00:04:03.201 position:50% align:center
Happy to do so.

00:04:03.284 --> 00:04:05.412 position:50% align:center
Right. Here's the
report you asked for.

00:04:06.579 --> 00:04:08.373 position:50% align:center
[LIN] It appears your
hunch was correct.

00:04:08.456 --> 00:04:11.084 position:50% align:center
The Kyougokukai have been
targeting Ikebukuro

00:04:11.167 --> 00:04:12.877 position:50% align:center
this whole time.

00:04:12.961 --> 00:04:15.130 position:50% align:center
They're a big
organization from Kansai

00:04:15.213 --> 00:04:17.924 position:50% align:center
dealing in narcotics
and firearms.

00:04:18.008 --> 00:04:20.635 position:50% align:center
I've inspected the weapons
they're smuggling into the city.

00:04:20.719 --> 00:04:24.305 position:50% align:center
They're the same make as the gun
that shot Andou, therefore--

00:04:24.389 --> 00:04:27.559 position:50% align:center
They must've found a way to
force Mitsuki into doing it.

00:04:27.642 --> 00:04:28.935 position:50% align:center
Most likely.

00:04:29.019 --> 00:04:31.896 position:50% align:center
Inciting violence to promote
trade and curry favor.

00:04:31.980 --> 00:04:33.273 position:50% align:center
How interesting.

00:04:33.356 --> 00:04:36.067 position:50% align:center
Keeping the Red Angels
and the G-Boys at odds.

00:04:36.151 --> 00:04:39.404 position:50% align:center
It weakens both sides as well as
damaging the Hidaka Group.

00:04:39.487 --> 00:04:40.905 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:04:40.989 --> 00:04:42.866 position:50% align:center
[LIN] Once the Red Angels
do the dirty work,

00:04:42.949 --> 00:04:44.409 position:50% align:center
they'll be discarded.

00:04:44.492 --> 00:04:48.246 position:50% align:center
After that, the yakuza has
free reign over Ikebukuro.

00:04:48.329 --> 00:04:50.081 position:50% align:center
So I imagine...

00:04:50.165 --> 00:04:53.335 position:50% align:center
Tohru Yoshimatsu.
He's an executive.

00:04:53.418 --> 00:04:56.504 position:50% align:center
The mob boss from Kansai
supplying the munitions.

00:04:57.797 --> 00:04:59.466 position:50% align:center
This guy's the mastermind.

00:04:59.549 --> 00:05:00.717 position:50% align:center
There's more.

00:05:00.800 --> 00:05:03.303 position:50% align:center
I suspect the presence
of another agent here.

00:05:03.386 --> 00:05:05.263 position:50% align:center
I'd wager that they're
the person who installed

00:05:05.347 --> 00:05:07.349 position:50% align:center
that tracking app on your phone.

00:05:07.432 --> 00:05:09.851 position:50% align:center
Somebody who could
get close to you.

00:05:09.934 --> 00:05:11.895 position:50% align:center
Someone on the inside.

00:05:11.978 --> 00:05:14.230 position:50% align:center
That individual likely
would have infiltrated

00:05:14.314 --> 00:05:16.483 position:50% align:center
Ikebukuro many
months ago,

00:05:16.566 --> 00:05:19.486 position:50% align:center
monitored the situation,
and waited patiently

00:05:19.569 --> 00:05:22.655 position:50% align:center
for the best moment
to spring into action.

00:05:22.739 --> 00:05:26.326 position:50% align:center
Be careful. I think they're
still watching you.

00:05:34.918 --> 00:05:37.253 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:05:38.630 --> 00:05:39.964 position:50% align:center
Makoto!

00:05:40.048 --> 00:05:41.424 position:50% align:center
Finally got you alone.

00:05:41.508 --> 00:05:43.385 position:50% align:center
Are you the only guard on duty?

00:05:45.804 --> 00:05:47.681 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO] You haven't
seen Mitsuki either.

00:05:47.764 --> 00:05:49.182 position:50% align:center
That's not good.

00:05:49.265 --> 00:05:51.393 position:50% align:center
[MASARU]
Yep.

00:05:51.476 --> 00:05:53.353 position:50% align:center
His folks can't
get ahold of him.

00:05:53.436 --> 00:05:56.314 position:50% align:center
His mom's worried
something fierce.

00:05:56.398 --> 00:05:58.400 position:50% align:center
Alright, let me
get this straight,

00:05:58.483 --> 00:06:01.111 position:50% align:center
he's the guy who
actually shot King.

00:06:01.194 --> 00:06:03.321 position:50% align:center
Even though everybody
believes you were the one

00:06:03.405 --> 00:06:04.698 position:50% align:center
who turned your back on us.

00:06:04.781 --> 00:06:06.741 position:50% align:center
I'm telling you I was set up.

00:06:06.825 --> 00:06:09.119 position:50% align:center
Mitsuki's my only witness.

00:06:09.202 --> 00:06:11.204 position:50% align:center
If he's alive, then we'll see.

00:06:11.287 --> 00:06:12.997 position:50% align:center
[MASARU exhales]

00:06:13.081 --> 00:06:15.208 position:50% align:center
What about Takashi's
condition right now?

00:06:15.291 --> 00:06:17.252 position:50% align:center
He's under good protection,
isn't he?

00:06:17.335 --> 00:06:19.421 position:50% align:center
[MASARU]
Yeah, we have that covered.

00:06:19.504 --> 00:06:23.550 position:50% align:center
But... he still hasn't woken up.

00:06:23.633 --> 00:06:25.427 position:50% align:center
Without a leader,

00:06:25.510 --> 00:06:28.763 position:50% align:center
each division of the G-Boys
is acting out on their own.

00:06:28.847 --> 00:06:32.100 position:50% align:center
There's no one to direct
them or hold them back.

00:06:32.183 --> 00:06:34.602 position:50% align:center
There's even talk
about a showdown.

00:06:34.686 --> 00:06:38.106 position:50% align:center
A final rendezvous with the
Red Angels at West Gate Park

00:06:38.189 --> 00:06:40.025 position:50% align:center
happening tonight.

00:06:40.108 --> 00:06:41.192 position:50% align:center
You're kidding!

00:06:41.276 --> 00:06:43.361 position:50% align:center
The other guys are
packing heat, you know!

00:06:43.445 --> 00:06:45.071 position:50% align:center
You'll be wiped out!

00:06:46.656 --> 00:06:47.907 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO gasps]

00:06:47.991 --> 00:06:49.868 position:50% align:center
I don't know where
they're coming from,

00:06:49.951 --> 00:06:53.121 position:50% align:center
but all of a sudden The G-Boys
have been getting pieces too.

00:06:53.204 --> 00:06:55.165 position:50% align:center
They even made me take one.

00:06:55.248 --> 00:06:57.042 position:50% align:center
[G-BOY E]
Masaru! You in there?

00:06:57.125 --> 00:06:58.418 position:50% align:center
I think that's my relief.

00:06:58.501 --> 00:07:00.253 position:50% align:center
You'd better run for it, Makoto!

00:07:00.337 --> 00:07:03.506 position:50% align:center
Hello? Where did he go? Hm?

00:07:07.260 --> 00:07:10.930 position:50% align:center
I just spotted Makoto!
Near Nishi Ichibangai!

00:07:11.014 --> 00:07:13.224 position:50% align:center
[pants]

00:07:13.308 --> 00:07:15.018 position:50% align:center
--[G-BOY F] Just stop!
--[G-BOY G] There he is!

00:07:15.101 --> 00:07:16.519 position:50% align:center
--Get back here!
--[G-BOY H] It's the traitor!

00:07:16.603 --> 00:07:17.979 position:50% align:center
[G-BOY I]
Don't let him get away!

00:07:18.063 --> 00:07:19.606 position:50% align:center
[G-BOY 12J]
Stop right there!

00:07:23.443 --> 00:07:24.652 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:07:28.782 --> 00:07:31.451 position:50% align:center
[G-BOYS shouting]

00:07:33.953 --> 00:07:34.704 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:07:34.788 --> 00:07:36.331 position:50% align:center
[gasps, groans]

00:07:41.711 --> 00:07:42.754 position:50% align:center
Hiroto?

00:07:42.837 --> 00:07:44.589 position:50% align:center
This way. Come with us!

00:07:47.342 --> 00:07:50.261 position:50% align:center
Well, well, so it's
the yakuza's fault.

00:07:50.345 --> 00:07:51.596 position:50% align:center
Just so we're clear,

00:07:51.680 --> 00:07:53.890 position:50% align:center
there's no room for you
in Ikebukuro anymore,

00:07:53.973 --> 00:07:55.141 position:50% align:center
so don't even try.

00:07:55.225 --> 00:07:56.851 position:50% align:center
That's fine by me.

00:07:56.935 --> 00:08:00.897 position:50% align:center
I'm busy enough as it is staking
out fresh turf for a new start.

00:08:00.980 --> 00:08:02.357 position:50% align:center
You got that right.

00:08:02.440 --> 00:08:04.484 position:50% align:center
We've actually been putting
together a crew in Kamata.

00:08:04.567 --> 00:08:06.069 position:50% align:center
It's shaping up pretty nicely.

00:08:06.152 --> 00:08:08.655 position:50% align:center
Turns out the men down there
know their way around a fight.

00:08:08.738 --> 00:08:11.157 position:50% align:center
If things are so great,
then why did you come back?

00:08:11.241 --> 00:08:13.493 position:50% align:center
I just wanted to hear
it from your side.

00:08:13.576 --> 00:08:16.454 position:50% align:center
The old stomping grounds
are on fire, aren't they?

00:08:16.538 --> 00:08:18.456 position:50% align:center
[CROW] The truth is,
we've been worried.

00:08:18.540 --> 00:08:19.874 position:50% align:center
Our calls weren't going through.

00:08:19.958 --> 00:08:22.502 position:50% align:center
And the fruit stand was a
wreck when we stopped by.

00:08:22.585 --> 00:08:24.462 position:50% align:center
[CROW]
So, Hiroto thought we'd hang out

00:08:24.546 --> 00:08:26.256 position:50% align:center
by the West Gate
until trouble started

00:08:26.339 --> 00:08:29.009 position:50% align:center
and then figured we'd find
you in the middle of it.

00:08:29.092 --> 00:08:30.176 position:50% align:center
[HIROTO]
What can I say?

00:08:30.260 --> 00:08:33.179 position:50% align:center
Guess I've started
using my head a little.

00:08:33.263 --> 00:08:36.725 position:50% align:center
Listen, there's something kinda
serious that I need to tell you.

00:08:36.808 --> 00:08:39.227 position:50% align:center
The person who sent
Shadow after you.

00:08:39.310 --> 00:08:41.021 position:50% align:center
--It was--
--Oh, I know.

00:08:41.104 --> 00:08:43.523 position:50% align:center
And I'm gonna settle
that score someday.

00:08:43.606 --> 00:08:45.150 position:50% align:center
But first things first.

00:08:45.233 --> 00:08:47.819 position:50% align:center
We need to put an end
to current madness.

00:08:47.902 --> 00:08:50.947 position:50% align:center
Hear that Makoto? We got you.

00:08:51.031 --> 00:08:52.240 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
Mm.

00:08:54.409 --> 00:08:56.870 position:50% align:center
There's no time left
to look for Mitsuki,

00:08:56.953 --> 00:09:00.457 position:50% align:center
and the Kyougokukai's been
gearing up the G-Boys as well.

00:09:00.540 --> 00:09:03.543 position:50% align:center
Like Lin said, they want
both sides to go down.

00:09:03.626 --> 00:09:05.462 position:50% align:center
We're fighting a dragon.

00:09:05.545 --> 00:09:07.088 position:50% align:center
So, what's our move?

00:09:09.424 --> 00:09:11.301 position:50% align:center
These'll help us
beat 'em for sure.

00:09:11.384 --> 00:09:13.303 position:50% align:center
Hey, thanks a lot Yoshimatsu!

00:09:13.386 --> 00:09:15.347 position:50% align:center
[YOSHIMATSU]
Nah, it's all business, kid.

00:09:15.430 --> 00:09:17.432 position:50% align:center
Just make sure you go crazy.

00:09:17.515 --> 00:09:19.768 position:50% align:center
You can always pay later.

00:09:21.061 --> 00:09:23.271 position:50% align:center
Why the long face, big guy?

00:09:23.355 --> 00:09:25.440 position:50% align:center
Say, you're from America,
aren't you?

00:09:25.523 --> 00:09:28.568 position:50% align:center
Those hoodlums over there mow
each other down every day.

00:09:28.651 --> 00:09:31.112 position:50% align:center
I believe you said
so yourself, didn't you?

00:09:31.196 --> 00:09:33.073 position:50% align:center
We don't have much of a choice.

00:09:33.156 --> 00:09:36.117 position:50% align:center
The other side has the full
support of the Hidaka Group.

00:09:36.201 --> 00:09:38.119 position:50% align:center
We might as well suit up.

00:09:38.203 --> 00:09:40.538 position:50% align:center
[YOSHIMATSU]
Isogai's got a good point there.

00:09:40.622 --> 00:09:42.874 position:50% align:center
Don't you want to
protect your family?

00:09:42.957 --> 00:09:45.960 position:50% align:center
Course I do. No matter the cost.

00:09:46.044 --> 00:09:47.295 position:50% align:center
[YOSHIMATSU]
Hm.

00:09:48.213 --> 00:09:52.008 position:50% align:center
--[phone buzzes]
--[TOMOMI] Uh? Huh?

00:09:52.092 --> 00:09:53.593 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
Isogai, it's me.

00:09:53.677 --> 00:09:55.637 position:50% align:center
[TOMOMI]
Thank goodness, I was worried.

00:09:55.720 --> 00:09:58.223 position:50% align:center
Are you okay? Where are you?

00:09:58.306 --> 00:10:00.350 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
I'm about to see Takashi.

00:10:00.433 --> 00:10:02.018 position:50% align:center
[TOMOMI]
Does that mean he's woken up?

00:10:02.102 --> 00:10:03.311 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
Yeah.

00:10:03.395 --> 00:10:05.772 position:50% align:center
We're going to figure out
how to stop the war.

00:10:05.855 --> 00:10:08.316 position:50% align:center
Really? Maybe I
should come along!

00:10:08.400 --> 00:10:09.693 position:50% align:center
[MAKOTO]
No, we're good.

00:10:09.776 --> 00:10:12.529 position:50% align:center
I'll hit you up once we
hash out the details.

